FBIS4-36656 "drnes113_j_94025" FBIS-NES-94-113 Daily Report 11 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Council Member Reiterates Abidance by Cease-Fire Council Member Reiterates Abidance by Cease-Fire JN1106192194 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 1700 GMT 11 Jun 94 JN1106192194 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Presidential Council member brother 'Abd-al-'Aziz 'Abd- al-Ghani has emphasized the Yemeni Government's commitment to the cease-fire. The government has also ordered a halt to hostilities against the rebels who violated the cease-fire for the second time. In a BBC interview broadcast yesterday evening, he [words indistinct] the commitment of the rebels. He indicated that if the rebels fail to comply, this means that the forces of legitimacy will have to defend themselves. Brother 'Abd-al-Ghani said the Republic of Yemen welcomes the mission of Lakhdar Brahimi, based on its acceptance of the UN Security council resolution on the situation in Yemen. Asked about acceptance of the resolution, brother 'Abd-al-Ghani said we [words indistinct] dialogue and we have borne [words indistinct] its [word indistinct] for nine [words indistinct] and are prepared to continue for stability and unity. But the separatist rebels were not serious and [words indistinct] and now we announced we are prepared for a dialogue with unionists within the [Yemeni] Socialist Party [YSP], not with those who proclaimed secession. Our dialogue with the unionists will be within the context of the Republic of Yemen and Constitutional legality, considering that the YSP is a patriotic party that has a presence throughout the republic's governorates. There are many top officials of the YSP in the Central Committee and in the House of Representatives, as well as party branch chiefs in the governorates who condemned the action taken by secessionists in the YSP.
